The order and format of how the flags field is unpacked in ncp_base is currently defined locally within the method; NcpBase::InsertPropertyHandler_THREAD_ON_MESH_NETS(...).

This location makes it difficult for host side implementation, as this method must be examined in order to learn the proper format.  Furthermore the maintenance of this order is challenged as the order must be defined at least in two locations. On the host side and here in the method named above.

The proposal is to define these fields in spinel.h where they can be accessed by both Host and NCP side equally.

For reference, the flags to which this issue is referring are;

    const static int kPreferenceOffset = 6;
    const static int kPreferenceMask = 3 << kPreferenceOffset;
    const static int kPreferredFlag = 1 << 5;
    const static int kSlaacFlag = 1 << 4;
    const static int kDhcpFlag = 1 << 3;
    const static int kConfigureFlag = 1 << 2;
    const static int kDefaultRouteFlag = 1 << 1;
